{
  "_README": [
    "Ground-truth fixture for the on-device E2E accuracy check.",
    "To ACTIVATE grading in CI: copy this file to 'costco_20260218_redact.expected.json'",
    "(drop the .template suffix), fill in the real values from the receipt, and commit it.",
    "The stem must match the .jpg: <stem>.jpg  <->  <stem>.expected.json.",
    "compare-e2e.py reads only the keys below; extra keys (like this one) are ignored.",
    "",
    "Field reference (all optional — omit a check to skip it):",
    "  merchant           exact-ish, fuzzy-normalized (case/space/punct-insensitive, >=0.85)",
    "  merchant_any_of    list of acceptable alternates for merchant",
    "  merchant_optional  true -> merchant always passes (presence-only)",
    "  date               exact string, same format the app emits (e.g. 2026-02-18)",
    "  total              exact decimal, compared numerically (e.g. 123.45)",
    "  critical_items     items that MUST appear; description is substring-matched,",
    "                     price exact; category substring-matched unless category_optional",
    "  known_failures     field names ('merchant'|'date'|'total'|'critical_items') to",
    "                     tolerate as expected-fail without failing the build"
  ],

  "merchant": "Costco",
  "merchant_any_of": ["Costco Wholesale"],
  "date": "2026-02-18",
  "total": "0.00",

  "critical_items": [
    {
      "description": "REPLACE_ME",
      "price": "0.00",
      "category": "Expenses:Groceries",
      "category_optional": true
    }
  ],

